President Trump visited Yuma, Arizona to celebrate the progress of the border wall construction. He praised the efforts of the Customs and Border Protection (CBP) and the Army Corps of Engineers in building the wall. The President highlighted the success of the wall in reducing illegal immigration, drug trafficking, and human trafficking. He also mentioned that the wall is equipped with anti-climb plates to prevent unauthorized entry. The President emphasized that the wall has been effective in securing the border and that the administration is on track to complete 300 miles of wall within two weeks. He also mentioned that the United States has funded the construction of 733 miles of wall in total. Additionally, the President addressed other topics such as the Post Office situation, Russia's interference in the 2016 election, the U.S.-China talks, and the upcoming Republican National Convention.